# Minimalist

Prefer small, reviewable moves.

## Red Flags

- Vendoring external scaffolding repos into this repository.
- Starting a full `src/` restructure while the task only asks for guardrails,
  docs, or one detector fix.
- Adding a framework when a standard-library helper or small function works.
- Changing detector thresholds and report language in the same PR without a
  clear reason.
- Introducing persistence or case-management systems before the reviewed-alert
  workflow is documented.

## Better Moves

- Add templates before adding complex process automation.
- Add one focused test around changed behavior.
- Split files only when a boundary is clear: clients, detectors, reporting,
  storage, dashboard export, or learning/corrections.
- Keep public-demo and private-operational modes explicit.
